description: Deletes an asset model. This action can't be undone. You must delete all assets created from an asset model before you can delete the model. Also, you can't delete an asset model if a parent asset model exists that contains a property formula expression that depends on the asset model that you want to delete. For more information, see Deleting assets and models in the IoT SiteWise User Guide.

parameters.name: assetModelId
parameters.description: The ID of the asset model to delete. This can be either the actual ID in UUID format, or else externalId: followed by the external ID, if it has one. For more information, see Referencing objects with external IDs in the IoT SiteWise User Guide.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: A unique case-sensitive identifier that you can provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. Don't reuse this client token if a new idempotent request is required. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

nested_items.name: assetModelStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the asset model, which contains a state ( DELETING after successfully calling this operation) and any error message.

nested_items.name: state
nested_items.description: The current state of the asset model.
